    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Detroit</placeName>
                <date>February 16th 1855</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I received yesterday<lb/> by American Express Company One case<lb/>
                of books &amp; to day by mail your favor of the<lb/>
                <date>10th</date> inst.</p>
            <p>By examining the contents of the case we find<lb/> the following books</p>
            <table cols="4" rows="5">
                <row>
                    <cell>6</cell>
                    <cell>daily Prayer Books</cell>
                    <cell/>
                    <cell>20</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>3</cell>
                    <cell>“ “ “</cell>
                    <cell>Mor. Marb Edg</cell>
                    <cell>$3.50</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>3</cell>
                    <cell>“ “ “</cell>
                    <cell>gold “</cell>
                    <cell>4.25</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>3</cell>
                    <cell>bibles</cell>
                    <cell>Mor. Marb “</cell>
                    <cell>9.00</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>1</cell>
                    <cell>set Pentateuch</cell>
                    <cell>(5 volumes)</cell>
                    <cell>16.50</cell>
                </row>
            </table>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Should you have intended to forward<lb/> any additional books this
                case did not<lb/> contain them.</p>
            <p>I shall endeavor when opportunities offer<lb/> to dispose of them &amp; also
                    <sic>aquaint</sic>
                <persName>Mr Adler</persName><lb/> of their arrival, in order to give him an<lb/>
                opportunity to exert himself for the sale of<lb/> them.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Any proceeds for the same recd. by me<lb/> will be forwarded to you
                immediately.<lb/> The Express charges I advanced were $4—</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><persName>Mr. Silberman</persName> resigned in consequence<lb/> of some
                misunderstanding with <persName>Mr Adler</persName><lb/> and as I was not present at
                the meeting<lb/> when this transpired &amp; have not for<lb/> several months past
                acted any more<lb/> as secretary I do not know whether <persName>Mr.<lb/>
                    Adler</persName> was directed by <add>קהל</add> to send<lb/> the proceedings for
                publication to <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName><lb/> or did so from his own
                accord.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Joseph Freedman</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Penn</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
